The paper deals with likelihood-based generative models, which are commonly used in machine learning for tasks such as image generation, anomaly detection, and out-of-distribution (OOD) detection. The focus of the paper is on improving OOD detection using generative models, which is a problem that falls under the categories of machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the limitations of likelihood-based models, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
